@khy is going through a bit of a rebrand—and @kyliejenner is opening up about it. As it stands, her brand is best known for collaborations and seasonal drops; but now it will move into a “fully realized, wardrobe-first fashion label.” Also getting refreshes are its website and social presence, which comes with a comprehensive new creative direction.
”I really wanted Khy to evolve into something more permanent and intentional,” Jenner tells ELLE. “ I’ve grown a lot since Khy launched, and my style is constantly evolving, so I want the brand to reflect that.”
Tap the link in bio to read our full interview with the mogul about her brand's new shift.

@topologie.official teams up with @miharayasuhiro_official for a laid-back capsule inspired by those quiet early hours. It blends MMY’s quirky, deconstructed style with Topologie’s functional gear, remixing playful motifs like Banana, Soft Serve, and Toothpaste across bags, straps, and phone accessories. The twist? Swappable handles that let you customize each piece on the go.⁠
⁠
The collection first dropped at a Seoul pop-up (April 16–22, 2026) and lands in Hong Kong on May 1 via topologie.com and select stores.

